---
title: Organic Chicken Cauli Bowls with Charred Grape Tomatoes, Chermoula & Creamy Tahini
description: This vegan bowl is not for the faint of heart: It’s full of textures and sauces and big flavors. From the curated spice blend to the herby-spicy-tangy chermoula, this one proves you don’t need meat to get bold flavor. We start with a big scoop of garlicky-zesty rice, top it with earthy, spice-roasted cauliflower and carrots, add juicy charred tomatoes, drizzles of cilantro-garlic-jalapeño sauce + creamy tahini, then sprinkle with crunchy almonds and bright lemon zest. Go big or go home!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/637d16955bebcc13b60fbf04-45d67a35.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/organic-chicken-cauli-bowls-637d16955bebcc13b60fbf04-97adf2a7.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/organic-chicken-cauli-bowls-637d16955bebcc13b60fbf04
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: African
nutrition:
  calories: 940 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 460 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss carrots and cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon}, @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Pat @organic chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add reserved garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

To bowl with reserved garlic, add cilantro, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and as much jalapeño as you like. Set chermoula aside.

In a second #small bowl{}, whisk together @tahini{2%tablespoon}, juice from half a lemon, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}. Add water 1 TBSP at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season tahini sauce with salt and pepper.

> Tahini will thicken at first as you add water but will then thin out again. We used 2 TBSP water for 2 servings, 3 TBSP for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over high heat. Add @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} and cook, undisturbed, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir tomatoes; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the lemon zest and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with roasted veggies and charred tomatoes. Drizzle with chermoula and tahini sauce. Garnish with @almonds{1/2%ounce} and remaining lemon zest. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise. Serve atop bowls.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.